The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Lucknow/Delhi, Feb. 2: Uttar Pradesh police today arrested a man wanted in connection with the 1993 train blasts that had killed hundreds across several states, ending the alleged suspects 16 years on the run after a long gun battle.          
	The arrest in Lucknow came a day after the police caught another terror suspect who masterminded the September 13, 2008, explosions in Delhi and was also involved in the Batla House encounter six days later.                   
	 Hyderabad (PTI): A fire broke in Park Superspeciality hospital on Tuesday morning in which an old patient who was on ventilator died before he could be rescued to a nearby hospital. Around 150 people, including 29 patients in ICU and emergency wards, escaped. The fire broke out because of a snag in the transformer, sources said.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): A tenant cannot claim money if he spends it on upgrading the premises without the landlords approval, Delhi High Court has said. It suggested that the tenant should get an approval in writing before renovating the house.                  
	 Melbourne (PTI): An Indian taxi driver was murdered in Auckland on Sunday. His taxi collided with a tree in Mount Eden around 1.20am, after which he was allegedly stabbed by the passenger. The way he was murdered would shock even criminals, police said.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Two men who allegedly posed as recovery agents of a private bank and cheated at least three persons, including a doctor, were arrested on Tuesday. The arrests came following a complaint filed by the doctor, who had taken a loan from ICICI Bank and was duped by the duo.
                                                                                                                                              
